{
  "name": "Skill Quality Gate (Edit)",
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "description": "Khi agent edit SKILL.md hiện có, check best practices, interconnection map, và install.sh profile consistency.",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      ".kiro/skills/**/SKILL.md"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "A SKILL.md was just edited. Verify the changes still meet quality standards per docs/skill-creation-best-practices.md:\n\n1. **Frontmatter**: name (kebab-case, = folder name), description (≤200 chars, starts with verb, contains trigger phrases + 'Use when...')\n2. **Scope**: Has 'This skill handles:' AND 'Does NOT handle:' with cross-references using → syntax\n3. **Decision Table**: At least 1 table mapping scenario → recommendation\n4. **Anti-Patterns**: Table of 'Agent thinks X → Reality Y'\n5. **Cross-References**: Related skills referenced, paths exist\n6. **Line Count**: SKILL.md < 300 lines (detail in references/)\n7. **Interconnection Map**: If scope boundaries changed, update docs/skill-interconnection-map.md accordingly\n8. **Profile Consistency**: If skill name changed, update install.sh profile function and README Installation Profiles table\n\nFix any issues found."
  }
}